description: The air smells of horses, but faintly as if none have passed this way too recently.  A fine sifting of sand coats the sloping floor where it meets the walls and the rock above you is almost completely hidden by a maze of crossbeams.  Metal bolts holding the beams to the ceiling and to each other reflect the wan light of distant lanterns.  The floor slants sharply down to the southwest.
title: [Zaerthu Tunnels]
